Dialogs.Dialog: 高嶺
There is some fruit punch over there. By the way, why is it called punch?
Yes, I was thinking the same. It's a strange name indeed.
Right? I wonder why it's not called fruit compote.
Com...pote?
At home, I call it fruit compote...
Huh?
But in a coffee shop, fruit compote is called fruit punch.
I've been curious lately. Do you think the same?
No, not really... I don't eat out that much, so I'm not sure.
I see. Okay, I'll remember that.
（What are you going to use that information for?）
高嶺
Is there anything else you don't like to eat besides fruit punch?
It's not that I don't like it, I just don't have it that much.
Then, what do you like?
You can't eat me.
I mean, anything with you is delicious, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Oh you... But, I think you're right. Except for bitter coffee.
I add sugar to it. About 10 spoonfuls.
That's too sweet.
Well then, I'll add salt too.
Now that's just weird.
高嶺
Come to think of it, do you want to put salt in your coffee?
Huh? What do you mean?
What other unusual drinks are you drinking?
I meant it as a joke... But, I drank chili sauce a long time ago.
Oh, nice. Do you love chili sauce?
I didn't liked it. I mistakenly thought it was tomato juice...
Was it next to the tomato juice? Then it was the same as Papa.
What do you mean?
Papa confused chili sauce as tomato juice.
Huh, I think I'll try it again, next time.
Fufu. Someday, when you meet Papa, can I tell him what you think?
I found a surprising use for chili sauce, and I tried it on a mackerel can.
高嶺
How was it?
It was pretty delicious.
How did it taste?
It was like mackerel muniel. It had a strong sour-flavor.
I guess it's a substitute for lemon.
Eh... Well, if you say so, that sounds right.
Fufu, why don't you try lemons next time?
...I will do that.
高嶺
Hey, you are living alone, right?
Hmm? Yeah, I live alone.
Do you do your housework appropriately?
Well, I do it like I know. I think I do it... well? I don't know.
Really?
It's okay. I do my chores when I need to.
Okay, then it's fine.
I wonder if it's not dangerous.
I don't think that's the case... I'm worried about you.
（I don't know what to say...）
高嶺
Hey, I'd like to ask you about your housework.
Oh, I'm doing my chores correctly.
You're also doing the cleaning, right? Are your rooms clean?
Well, from your point of view it might not look like it's clean, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Now I'm getting worried...
I think it's okay, though. I know where most of my things are, and there are no cockroaches...
Kyaa~!
Hmm?
N-nothing...
（You don't like them, do you...）
高嶺
I'm being so persistent lately, will you forgive me?
Hmm? What do you mean?
When I was asking about your housework...
No problem, I know you care about me.
How about washing your clothes?
I try to do it sometimes, but...
Huh, you don't do it everyday?
Almost... every day. It's just me, so it's not that much.
Hmm...
（You don't have to worry that much...）
高嶺
Hey, I was thinking recently...
What's on your mind?
I think I should help you with your housework.
Huh? You want to help me in my house, ▲高嶺＊＊▲!?
...I knew you won't like the idea... Can't I?
I not against it, but... I think it's not good doing that to you. And your parents could get worried.
Why would Mama and Papa worry?
I don't know why... I'm just sure.
All I'm asking is if you need my help, so I think it'll all be good.
Okay... I'll keep it in mind for future reference, okay?
（I see... Are you really looking forward for it?）
高嶺
...I'd like to talk to you about dishes involving fish.
Cooking, huh?... I don't think I'll too helpful. But if you want my help, I'll be glad.
Okay, thank you. I tried to prepare the fish, and...
Was it alive?
No, not really. The fish lying on the cutting board seems to be staring at me.
Yes, that happens sometimes. It's a little scary when you see the fish at the supermarket.
When I looked into its eyes, I couldn't move my kitchen knife at all...
You could close you eyes. But it would be impossible to cook or be dangerous.
What should I do then?
Then it's not a cooking problem. Let's see...
Hmm...
It's about the fish dishes we were talking about before.
高嶺
Ah, yes.
In other words, are you afraid of the fish's eyes?
It's not the eyes themselves, but I can seem to hear its voice...
A voice... from the fish?
"What are you doing?", "What are you doing to me?"... That kind of voice.
You can't actually hear it, can you?
Of course I can. Doesn’t happen to you? I even hear stuffed animals.
I don't have stuffed animals in my room...
It feels like the stuffed bunny will say "Welcome back", "Did you have fun?". I can hear things like that.
I'm not afraid of that.
Oh, of course.
It's about the fish dishes we were speaking about.
高嶺
Ah, yes. Did you think of a good way?
Why don't you turn your face when you buy it?
If that's the case, I can't see how fresh it is... And it's not a fundamental solution.
Why don't you wear sunglasses when you cook? You won't even see the eyes of the fish.
Then I would look like a shady person.
Paint the fish's eyes. Even magic paint should work.
That would be a little cruel...
But they are already dead.
Even so... it's not good to do that.
Well, you might be right...
I want to talk about the problem of cooking fish.
高嶺
Ah, yes.
You should hide the eyes of the fish, cover them with a cloth.
I've already done that, but I can still feel them watching me. Those eyes under the cloth... gazing at my soul.
Then... Ah, I know!
What's wrong?
I will scold it. Hey you, don't bother ▲高嶺＊＊▲ anymore!
You're... to the fish...?
That's right, don't scare other people's girlfriends!
Now the fish looks angry... That's why you can eat it now.
...Ah, that's right!
I feel a pity for it. But... I think it's okay.
I will cook it while thinking you are by my side. If I can do that, I will be fine.
高嶺
There's something I'd like to tell you.
What's wrong? Is everything alright?
It's just that I often don't understand the words everyone uses...
Sometimes I miss myself in the conversation.
Ah, I see. It's okay, I can help you with some words.
Thank you. Then... what is "Gachi"?
"Gachi" is...
How do you write its kanji?
...Kanji?
It's a fair game, seriously. I understand the meaning, but I don't understand its kanji.
Gachi, uh... "Ga" means I, and "chi" means... blood?
I see! That's great, thank you.
...I'm sorry ▲高嶺＊＊▲. That was a joke...
高嶺
Well, you know, I was thinking there's another popular word I don't understand...
What kind of word?
What does girl's power mean?
Well, ▲高嶺＊＊▲ has high girl power.
My friend told me that too. Is that something good?
Of course, it's something that gives you high power.
Then, are you high on male power?
...I wonder about that. It's something different from the boyfriend's power.
Huh?
Whatever!
...Ah well, that was weird.
高嶺
Hey, do you know what kind of person is "Pane"?
It's Marzipan.
Yes, that's the one. I really understand what it means, but I think it should be called Pa-nee-san.
I don't think "Pa-nee-san" is the right way to call it.
You don't have to laugh at my idea so much...
Sorry, sorry.
You mean... it isn't about people?
Indeed, it might be a person.
Oh, really?
And, it may not be a person.
Huh? Oh, come on! Stop messing around.
Hahaha.
高嶺
Emm, there are some words that I still don't understand. When do you use "Disuru"?
I don't want to be dissed by you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
THIS can be done? THIS is passive? I wonder what it means...
No, no. It's not "This", but "Dis".
Oh, then that's a bad thing to say.
Was it originally a rapper term?
Rap? Is it a music term?
Well, I wonder about that...
I see. Okay, I'll see you later...
（This thing is one of your good points, ▲高嶺＊＊▲）
